spec: asyncio_extra79
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(asyncio)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio.html — Python asyncio module documentation"
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio-sync.html — asyncio Synchronization Primitives"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/asyncio/locks.py"
  notes:
    - "This spec extends asyncio_extra78.zspec.zsdl."
    - "This spec covers: wave 244 theme — asyncio Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore/Condition acquire/release/wait code attributes. NEW in extra79: Semaphore.acquire.__code__.co_name=='acquire'; Semaphore.acquire.__code__.co_argcount==1 (self only; blocking and timeout are keyword-only); Semaphore.release.__code__.co_name=='release'; Semaphore.release.__code__.co_argcount==1 (self only); BoundedSemaphore.release.__code__.co_name=='release'; BoundedSemaphore.release.__code__.co_argcount==1 (self only); Condition.wait.__code__.co_name=='wait'; Condition.wait.__code__.co_argcount==1 (self only); Condition.notify.__code__.co_name=='notify'; Condition.notify.__code__.co_argcount==2 (self + n); Condition.notify_all.__code__.co_name=='notify_all'; Condition.notify_all.__code__.co_argcount==1 (self only); Condition does NOT define acquire or release (it uses __aenter__/__aexit__ for the context manager protocol). All verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.Semaphore.acquire.__code__.co_name == 'acquire'. Semaphore.acquire is a coroutine method in asyncio/locks.py; its code object co_name is 'acquire'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.Semaphore.acquire.__code__.co_argcount == 1. Only self is a positional parameter; blocking and timeout are keyword-only. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.Semaphore.release.__code__.co_name == 'release'. Semaphore.release is a plain method in asyncio/locks.py. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.Semaphore.release.__code__.co_argcount == 1. Only self is a positional parameter. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.BoundedSemaphore.release.__code__.co_name == 'release'. BoundedSemaphore overrides release to enforce the upper bound; the override is named 'release'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.BoundedSemaphore.release.__code__.co_argcount == 1. Only self is a positional parameter. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.Condition does NOT define acquire or release — it uses __aenter__/__aexit__ for async with. Condition.wait, notify, notify_all are defined in Condition.__dict__. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.Condition.wait.__code__.co_name == 'wait'. Condition.wait is a coroutine method in asyncio/locks.py. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.Condition.wait.__code__.co_argcount == 1. Only self is a positional parameter. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.Condition.notify.__code__.co_name == 'notify'. Condition.notify is a plain method in asyncio/locks.py. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.Condition.notify.__code__.co_argcount == 2. notify takes self and n (number of waiters to notify, default 1) as positional parameters. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.Condition.notify_all.__code__.co_name == 'notify_all'. Condition.notify_all is a plain method in asyncio/locks.py. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.Condition.notify_all.__code__.co_argcount == 1. Only self is a positional parameter. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
  created_at: "2026-04-10T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

